					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 12(1/2) <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold for burning a perpetual lamp before the image of Chandraśēkhara-Perumāḷ in the temple, by <hi rend="bold">Pañchavanmādēvi the consort (araiśi) of Araiyaṉ Mahimālayaṉ</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka-Muttaraiyaṉ.</hi> The <hi rend="italic">maṉṟāḍikkalanai</hi> of the place received the amount and agreed to supply an <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee daily for the purpose. This is probably an inscription of <hi rend="bold">Uttama-Chōḷa.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
